{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Bo2p83LUa6fY2bWzXvxECp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pods have a `crdb-cluster-certs` secret mounted, even though `kubectl get secrets` didn't show any secrets in the namespace. Maybe the secret existed and was recently deleted (as mentioned in the task note: \"an external process may have deleted or altered TLS secrets during this task\").\n\nWait - actually, the pods are running AND have cert files in `/cockroach/cockroach-certs/`. This means the certs are being served from the volume. But `kubectl get secrets` showed \"No resources found\". \n\nOh wait - the problem description says \"an external process may have deleted or altered TLS secrets during this task\". So likely the secret was deleted after the pods started. \n\nThe pods still have the old certs mounted in their volumes from before the deletion. So my plan is to generate new node certificates using the CA from the toolbox, recreate the secret with those new certs, and then do a rolling restart of the pods to pick up the updated certificates.\n\nI'll work through this step by step: generate a new node key and CSR using the existing node.cnf, sign it with the CA for 365 days, handle the client root certs, create the Kubernetes secret, and finally restart the pods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":908,"cache_read_input_tokens":32030,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":908},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5fffa0d-1115-4cb1-880a-3ef3b2645441","uuid":"7ec0741a-3b7e-4720-afda-583637e2254a","request_id":"req_011CcQ7bQUa91oLvJ1figjb5"}
